Subject: [PATCH] remove Fish from TTS provider + model validation lists

Part of the Fish Audio retirement. After chris-claim-status was
migrated to ElevenLabs (see voice-engine main commit 28d7763 and
earlier frontend fix 72d9917 in voiceagentfront), no agent in Aurora
is on Fish and the Python pipeline's Fish branch is being removed in
the same PR on the voice-engine side.

This patch cleans up the Lambda's validation lists and the agent
schema returned to the frontend. The frontend auto-updates from the
schema — no frontend change needed.

Deployed out-of-band to medcloud-voice-api on 2026-04-20 21:55 UTC.

Post-deploy verification (/api/agent-schema):
  tts_providers:  ['elevenlabs']
  tts_models_by_provider:
    {'elevenlabs': ['eleven_turbo_v2_5', 'eleven_flash_v2_5', 'eleven_multilingual_v2']}
  tts_models (flat): ['eleven_turbo_v2_5', 'eleven_flash_v2_5', 'eleven_multilingual_v2']
---
 src/index.mjs | 3 +--
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/index.mjs b/src/index.mjs
--- a/src/index.mjs
+++ b/src/index.mjs
@@ -399,12 +399,11 @@
   'claude-sonnet-4-5-20250514',
 ];
-const VALID_TTS_PROVIDERS = ['elevenlabs', 'fish'];
+const VALID_TTS_PROVIDERS = ['elevenlabs'];
 // Per-provider model lists. Keep flat VALID_TTS_MODELS for legacy consumers
 // that don't know about providers yet.
 const TTS_MODELS_BY_PROVIDER = {
   elevenlabs: ['eleven_turbo_v2_5', 'eleven_flash_v2_5', 'eleven_multilingual_v2'],
-  fish: ['s1', 's2', 's2-mini', 's2-pro'],
 };
 const VALID_TTS_MODELS = Object.values(TTS_MODELS_BY_PROVIDER).flat();
 const VALID_STT_PROVIDERS = ['deepgram', 'elevenlabs'];
